> Re: Epic Trains....Mwhahahahaha</span><hr size=1> Ok for those Lower Guk fans. Was in a group in the Frenzy camp with my warrior when the server went down. When I finally could get back on which was about 2 hours later I logged into the area just outside frenzy room. There was not a soul to be found near me. So I called the train to zone. Being a warrior and not having a SoW there was but one way out, Run it. As I hit the jail area near safe hall there was a ranger who logged in and had his own train from near the lord room. All of these aggroed on me too. There was not a executioner group nor a bedroom group. Just one group at the zone. So to make a long story short, my froglock train started outside of frenzied room, had about 9 adds from ranger who died in jail, I ran through executioner camp area, passed ass/sup, passed the gargoyles and wizards on the ledge, passed skeletons, through bats and bedroom all the way to zone.<br>
<br>
Even though I called a train the zone group did not zone, they waited in hopes of getting a nice mob there at the zone. So as I went passed them and zoned they were anxiously waiting. The train was so large (one of the zone members said at least 40 frogs) that they filled the area between the zone group and the zoneline keeping the zone group from being able to zone out. They all had a horrible and quick death. Fortunately some of them had a good sense of humor since I called the train and congratulated me on the largest train they had ever seen.<br>
