 Well, being the stupid n00b I was at the time, I shouted in reply &quot;Really? Does it cost anything for tickets?&quot;  Then someone shouted &quot;He's a goner!&quot; And I shouted &quot;Who's a goner?&quot; And at least 3 peeps said &quot;/sigh&quot; So I'm waiting by the zone for about 30 seconds, and suddenly I see what looks like a black cloud approaching me. Well, let me just tell you what was in that train. Actually its not that hard to explain. As a joke, the people went around the ENTIRE ZONE and aggroed EVERYTHING, including Dvinn the trainer the royal guard... the works. So I started typing &quot;Well theres the train, but why are Orcs riding it....&quot; but before I could finish my sentence, I was trampled in literally .000000000001 seconds. Ever have one of those times when your standing there and then the next second your laying on the ground watching endless amounts of mobs trample over your poor pathetic corpse? Well that was one of those times!  And it doesn't end there, no! My torture continues. I run back to CB and zone in only to find that gigantic train waiting at the zone for me. There was at least 50 corpses around the enterance to Crushbone, and I was marveling at the amount of Orcs and bodies when I heard &quot;Orc Stomp, Orc Kill&quot; blah blah blah. Well needless to say, I died. And by the end of that hour, I was level five again. What an adventure that was! But hey, I learned something useful that day! I learned what a TRAIN really is.<br>
